        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:29PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wharton, or 13 miles south of Madison, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Van, Wharton, Bald Knob, Whitesville, Sylvester, Seth, Stickney,
Prenter, Sharples, and Jeffrey.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
